
[1]reed

   REED, n.

   1. The common name of many aquatic plants; most of them large grasses,
   with hollow jointed stems, such as the common reed of the genus Arundo,
   the bamboo, &c. The bur-reed is of the genus Sparganium; the Indian
   Flowering reed of the genus Canna.

   2. A musical pipe; reeds being anciently used for instruments of music.

   3. A little tube through which a hautboy, bassoon or clarinet is blown.

   4. An arrow, as made of a reed headed.

   5. Thatch.
